You spoke to a guide, not a GM. Guides do not have access to any logs as they are sitting in their homes, just like you and me. They are not paid employees as GMs are. Simply volunteer customer service folk that are players like everyone else.<P>You may have missed it, but notice this line:<BR>[Tue May 08 23:19:23 2001] Zelorixa BROADCASTS, 'All zones are back up! Thank you for your patience tonight! If you died in Skyshrine, Wakening Lands, Plane of Mischief, Eastern Wastes or Crystal Caverns as a result of the crash, please petition for resurrection.'<P>What that would tell me is that before you even dropped Naggy, 5 zones went down (a couple of them probably very populated). Even if only half the people dropped petitioned, that would be around 100 petitions waiting to be answered before you even sent your tell, and probably almost all of them looking for a rez. All that with one guide online and a GM (who was obviously there to broadcast the zones being back up). I'm surprised the guide even sent you a response asking you to petition.<P>Also, and I guess this could be taken as a flame which it is not intended to be - more insight than anything - why is it a guides fault if you take ninja looters on a dragon raid with you?<P>/boggle<P>A "/petition I think someone ninja looted Nagafen on my raid... could you please have a GM check the logs if at all possible since ninja looting is a direct violation of the play nice polices.  Thank you" probably would have more than done the trick for you...
