The point Corpheous was trying to make was that the guide chose to circumvent a simple &#8216;yes&#8217; or &#8216;no&#8217; question with some crap.  How hard is it to respond to a tell?  You hit the r button and type in 'yes' or 'no'.  It would have been less than a second to respond to that and the whole ordeal would have been over with.  If the guide didn't know whether Naggy always dropped coin or not, say so.  Again, it doesn't take long to do that either.  Don't be a dick and say 'Petition please' when someone who's been on a raid for x amount of hours and needs to sleep wants to know a simple yes or no question.<P>I know I sound like I'm not being too considerate of the fact that the guide might have had a bunch of tells incoming and petitions to deal with on top of that...but the fact of the matter is that when you sign on to be a Guide, that is what you have to expect and deal with.  Period.  Guides aren't required to be polite to everyone because they don't have their jobs at stake but on the other hand, you do know what kind of scenario you are getting into when you sign up.  So getting curt and flat out rude to people in game is unacceptable IMHO because you are supposed to be there to help others out so that they can get the most fun out of the game within reason.  Responding the way the guide did and from the tone of Corpheous&#8217; post, I gathered that it created some dissatisfaction instead of satisfaction and in no way helped out the situation.<P>--------------------<P>Laras Shantar - Lvl 53 Half Elf Druid<BR>Yiniar Shantar - Lvl 48 Erudite Necromancer<BR>Malf Shantar - Lvl 34 Half Elf Ranger<BR>Tuladin - Lvl 28 Wood Elf Rogue
