<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I was a guide for a while(yeah, I'm 14, and I was a guide, they don't check ages very well  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">), and here's a rule I learned right away: Answer questions from players in this order:<BR>1. Petitions<BR>2. /Say<BR>3. /Tell<BR>4. /Shout, /Ooc... only respond to shout or ooc in tells and only if it's for disrupting the zone.<P>You may think that a simple yes/no question would be simple to answer, but it can get tough if oh, say, 10 people have a yes/no question and there's a guide and a gm on, and all of em decide to go with the guide cause they don't want to bother the gm...  Then it gets annoying.  Most guides have a hotkey that's /r please petition any problems/questions.. or something like that.  I know I did   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>-Saethan<P><I>Your basis everything belongs to us!</I>
