Corpheous <P>You <B>didn't</B> /tell the GM.  You sent a /tell to the <B>Guide</B>.<P>In your log you include a /who of GM's, the output from that shows <I>one</I> GM and <I>one</I> Guide online.  Your log also shows the following:<P><STRONG>Abednego shouts, 'god that is unbelievable...wee my first bad gm experience *a tear*' </STRONG><P>Your friend petitioned and talked to the <B>GM</B>.  You sent a /tell to the <B>Guide</B> - someone who had <I>not</I> been dealing with your raid's problem.<P>So, there were 2 customer service reps online. One a Verant employee, one a volunteer with <B>far</B> less powers.  You have said that your raid had already discussed the problem with the GM for an hour and were not satisfied with the outcome.  <P>At the same time, the same GM had now moved on to spamming the server with the message:<P><STRONG>[Tue May 08 23:19:23 2001] Zelorixa BROADCASTS, 'All zones are back up! Thank you for your patience tonight! If you died in Skyshrine, Wakening Lands, Plane of Mischief, Eastern Wastes or Crystal Caverns as a result of the crash, please petition for resurrection.'</STRONG><P>So.  The GM you've already dealt with is now dealing with the aftermath of a 5-zone crash.  We already know that there are only <B>two</B> CS reps on and, we can assume, that both of them are going to taking these petitions for Rez's.<P>At that point you send the Guide, the CS Rep who <I>wasn't</I> involved in your dispute, a /tell even though he's now dealing with all the Rez petitions that GM's system message would have illicited.<P>I don't know the right or wrong of your Ninja-Loot problem, but it doesn't take much common sense to see that when you have two CS Reps trying to deal with a 'disaster' recovery, <B>added</B> to the fact that one of them had just given your raid's problem a full hour's attention, you are not likely to get anything other than the response you did if you <I>then</I> decide to ignore the /petition procedure and bug the <I>other</I> CS rep direct.<P>In short - I think you should have put in a /petition and waited your turn.
