I think Corpheous was pretty clear about what went on. Naggy was killed, when she was looted, there was no coin, and none of the especially good items. The raiders suspected that there was a ninja looter, but weren't sure. The fact that there was no coin seemed to be the clinching bit of evidence, so Corpheous tried to check on it.<P>Now, the raid leader petitioned and talked with the GM (not clear, maybe he talked to a guide). The raid leader talked for an hour (not clear, maybe it took an hour for the petition to get answered). After that hour, Corpheous sent a tell to the Guide, and the guide refused to answer, telling Corpheous to petition. Corpheous got all pissy, saying the Guide should answer a simple yes or no question, and refused to follow the Guides instruction until the Guide threatened him with a warning.<P>Corpheous is clearly in the wrong here. First of all, it is not clear that the guide in question has anything to do with the raids petition about Naggy. When your petition gets answered, it gets answered by one person, not the whole staff at once.<P>Supposing the guide is the same one that dealt with the issue. He doesn't know who Corpheous is. To him, Corpheous is just a queue jumper. There is no way for him to know there is any relation between Corpheous and the raid leader. By trying to insert himself into a discussion, Corpheuos just confuses things.<P>Now, the simple yes or no question. How can the guide know for sure, off the top of his head, whether or not Naggy always drops coin? Probably, sure. Definitely? gotta check. So it isn't a simple yes or no. Also, he probably does have a hotkeyed: /r Please use petition, not tells, so it is actually easier for him to tell you to petition than answer the yes or no question. I wouldn't be surprised if he also has hotkeyed: /r If you send a tell after being told to petition, you will get a warning, So that comment could also be easier than answering yes or no.<P>I have to wonder, did the raid leader never mention that no coin dropped when his petition was answered? If not, why not? If so, why was Corpheous asking again? Did the raid leader really lack communication skills? How did he get to be raid leader, then?
