<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have not been in on any raids, but I am confused.<P>I was under the impression that one could not loot a critter for a period of time after the kill unless one was in on the kill and got the exp (if any) for it.<P>I can understand how a group could be fighting a lot of critters and not manage to loot in time, but by the time Naggy was killed, it would seem likely there wasn't much other fighting going on.  How is it possible to ninja loot in this case?<P>Also, I frequently loot dead critters when there is no one around.  I am low level (10 max) so there really aren't any great items, but what are the rules on this?  I could see myself thinking "Gee, they are done with naggy, and the body is still there.  Maybe they didn't want some of the stuff." and loot to see what is there.  I would have asked the groups since they were still standing around, but I can see how someone might not think of it.<P>I thought ninja looting was when someone in the group kept taking the stuff, or when you had to fight a ton of critters so that the time ran out while you were still fighting.<P>--------------------<P>Josef - Servant of Balance
</FONT>
